The paper deals with the complexity of regular abstractions of languages recognized by one-counter automata, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). The use of automata and the study of their properties also falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper involves the analysis of computational complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.TC) and logic (cs.LO). The construction of NFA involves the use of algorithms, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT).
